\begin_layout Section*
OBJECTIVE OF THE PROJECT
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
A.
 Description of the problem:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The prevalence of social networking sites (SNS) has significantly increased
 over the past decade, reshaping how students interact and communicate.
 The rise of platforms like Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram has revolutionized
 the way students connect with peers, share information, and express themselves
 online.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The popularity of social networking sites began to soar around the mid-2000s,
 with Facebook emerging as a dominant player in the market.
 Over the years, the landscape has evolved, with new platforms and features
 continuously being introduced.
 This rapid growth has had a profound impact on student life, influencing
 their social interactions, academic pursuits, and overall well-being.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The outbreak of the COVID-19 pandemic further amplified the role of social
 networking sites in students lives, as quarantine and social distancing
 measures forced them to rely more on these platforms for socializing and
 staying connected with friends and classmates.
 This increased reliance on social networking sites has led to changes in
 how students manage their time, with many spending more hours online than
 before.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As a result, we have witnessed a significant shift in student's social habits
 and behaviors, with social networking sites playing a central role in shaping
 their identities and relationships.
 Understanding these changes is crucial for educators, parents, and policymakers
 to support students in navigating the digital landscape and ensuring a
 healthy balance between online and offline interactions.
\end_layout

