\begin_layout Standard
The impact of 5G on students in India is expected to be significant, providing
 them with access to faster and more reliable internet connectivity.
 This could facilitate enhanced learning experiences through online education
 platforms, improved access to educational resources, and the ability to
 collaborate on projects remotely.
 Additionally, 5G could enable new learning technologies such as augmented
 reality (AR) and virtual reality (VR), creating more immersive and interactive
 educational experiences.
 However, challenges such as ensuring equitable access to 5G-enabled devices
 and addressing potential distractions from increased connectivity may also
 need to be addressed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hence we can clearly sees that the impact of 5g is huge among the students
 and in the same time we want to examine or wanted to know the impact of
 internet usage among students.
 Here we want to collect the data about the preference of the students on
 which platform they prefer to spend time and also the many things like
 is there any relationship between their sleep hours, is there any impact
 for excessive use of internet any many more.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The first part of the questionnaire included questions regrading personal
 information of the respondents, like their age, gender, profession, and
 where do they live.
 The second part of the questionnaire included questions regarding the usage
 like how many hours they use internet and favorite platform ,why they uses
 the internet for and many more .the third part of the questionnaire included
 some basic behavior of a students like do they like to read? whats your
 opinion about politics and are they recognized themselves as an introvert
 or extrovert etc .
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
B.
 Target Population and Sampling Frame
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Our target population was the people living in Kolkata and its surrounding
 places and also villages, as we are interested to know the change in their
 internet usage habits in recent times.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
C.
 Sampling Scheme
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Looking at the data we were able to gather from the survey, we realized
 that our responses were filled with a majority of respondents belonging
 to the age-group of 18-25 years.
 As a result of which, we decided to proceed with simple random sampling
 (SRS) mechanism (where each element in the population has an equal probability
 of being selected to the sample).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
D.
 Design of the Questionnaire
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To design the Questionnaire we followed this steps: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Introduction: Start with an introduction explaining the purpose of the study
 and ensuring confidentiality and voluntary participation.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
General Information (RQ general): Age: __________ & Gender: Male / Female
 / Other / Prefer not to say
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Educational Level: High School / College / Postgraduate Frequency 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Impact of Social Media Use (RQ1): How frequently do you use social media?
 (Multiple choice: Several times a day / Once a day / A few times a week
 / Rarely / Never)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How do you think frequent use of social media impacts your daily life? (Open-end
ed) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Types of Social Media Used and Screen Time (RQ2): Which social media platforms
 do you use regularly? (Multiple choice: Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, Snapchat,
 etc.) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How many hours per day do you spend on social media? (Open-ended)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Purpose of Social Media Use (RQ3): Do you use social media more for entertainmen
t or educational purposes? (Multiple choice: Entertainment / Educational
 / Both equally) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Social Media Addiction and Academic Performance (RQ4): Do you feel addicted
 to social media? (Yes / No) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Do you think social media addiction affects your academic performance? (Yes
 / No / Not sure) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Distractions and Coping Mechanisms (RQ5): Do you feel distracted from other
 activities due to social media use? (Yes / No) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Behavioral Changes (RQ6): Have you noticed any behavioral changes in yourself
 due to excessive social media use? (Open-ended) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Conclusion: Thank the participants for their time and provide contact informatio
n for any questions or concerns.
 Optional: Include a section for additional comments or feedback.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Although, we faced several problems at first like the correct order of the
 questions and actually what kind of queations are valid and etc.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
E.
 Follow-up of the process
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
During the initial stages of data collection, we observed that a major portion
 of the recorded responses was from the age group of 14-30 years which was
 quite obvious as young adults are generally more accustomed to these kind
 of services than the elderly section of the population.
 Hence we tried to circulate the google form among people falling in those
 age groups.
 We also asked everyone to re-share our questionnaire, especially among
 those people in their contacts belonging to our required age group, so
 that our reach and range of data increases.
\end_layout

